task.summary: Initial commit giving rough idea of the game loop and the methods I'll need.
Got platform obstacles moving. Need to figure out how to apply friction and still have the ball move right. Then I'll break up the platforms and implement the 'remove_platform' function

Turns out friction aint so great for rolling balls. Made a custom velocity function for the agent which dampens the x-velocity each step. Also added another velocity function for the agent to keep it static when the game starts. Platforms are now split up.
Reward function implemented, game is now complete. Onto the function that transforms the pixels on screen into a smaller matrix to feed into the net. Also need to do some refactoring.
format screen render to numpy matrix of 0's and 1's completed.
changed colours to make background black, agent cyan and platforms white, still processed to be a grayscale representation of surface.
Implemented the example for reinforcement learning found on Outlace.com, I will mofidy this to make it work - just palceholder for now.

Changed the network to make it like the DeepMind atari one. This involved editing the dimensions of the game screen such that there is no information loss between conv layers w/o necessity for pooling layers.
Reference point, crashes trying to fit to model. Need to revise the q-learning algorithm I've implemented to take 4 last frames as state.
I think it works!! Just need to train it now. Getting 5fps on my macbook - going to look at AWS GPU instances.
